newsitem.title: USA: FCOJ futures end up slightly but trade thin.
newsitem.headline: FCOJ futures end up slightly but trade thin.

text.p: FCOJ futures inched higher on light local buying and a dearth of selling interest, but volume was estimated at only 2,750 lots.
Benchmark September settled up 0.85 cent at 121.10 cents a lb after trading from 121.50 to 119.25 cents. November closed 0.40 firmer at 115.65, with the rest 0.25 lower to up 0.70.
"The specs and the funds are still buying and the market is holding support levels (119.00 for September)," said Keven Marshburn, an analyst with Fimat Futures.
He said if the weekly Florida movement number, released after the market closes Thursday, and supply and demand data remain strong, prices will maintain current levels.
He pegged resistance for September delivery around 124.00
USDA will release its next estimate for the crop in October.
